HEADWORD: Slyly
<hw>Sly"ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>In a sly manner; shrewdly;
craftily.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Honestly and <qex>slyly</qex> he it spent.</q>
